metadata.editComments:
If you're wondering why the YouTube video has no melody in it, that's because "Sony Music Entertainment" has blocked all copies of the original version. The only versions uploaded onto YouTube are the sped up ones, the remixes, and the piano interpretations. Which is why I'm surprised my instrumental version wasn't automatically flagged and blocked by YouTube's content ID match. I assume they'll find it sooner or later and remove it, but it stands. For now.

Who the hell blocks their songs on YouTube, anyways? Do they not want people to hear their song? If Sony comes after this I'll cry.
